h [[Warren Luff]] in car 26. After the 2007 season Gurr retired with recurring injuries from a serious accident earlier in his career. He was replaced by [[Marcus Marshall]] in the #26 Irwin backed Ford, and he has since not raced in the series.\n\n==Career results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! Season\n! Series\n! Position\n! Car\n! Team\n|-\n! 2000/01\n| [[2000/2001 Australian Super Touring Championship|Australian Super Touring Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" | 5th\n| [[Ford Mondeo]]<br>[[Nissan Primera]]\n| Knight Racing<br>Hi-Tech Motorsport\n|-\n! 2001\n| [[2001 Australian Drivers' Championship|Australian Drivers Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background: #ffdf9f\" | '''3rd'''\n| [[Reynard Motorsport|Reynard]] 94D [[Holden]]\n| Ralt Australia\n|-\n! 2002\n| [[2002 Australian Super Touring Series|Australian Super Touring Series]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background: #ffffbf\" | '''1st'''\n| [[BMW E36|BMW 320i]]\n| [[Paul Morris Motorsport|NEMO Racing]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | 2003\n| [[2003 Australian Formula 3 Championship|Australian Formula 3 Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" | 8th\n| [[Dallara]] F301 [[Alfa Romeo]]\n| Piccola Scuderia Corse\n|-\n| [[2003 V8 Supercar Championship Series|V8 Supercar Championship Series]]\n| align=\"center\" | 67th\n| [[Holden VX Commodore]]\n| [[Paul Morris Motorsport]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | 2004\n| [[2004 Konica Minolta V8 Supercar Series|Konica Minolta V8 Supercar Series]]\n| align=\"center\" | 14th\n| [[Holden VX Commodore]]\n| Smiths Trucks<br>[[Holden Young Lions]] \n|-\n| [[2004 V8 Supercar Championship Series|V8 Supercar Championship Series]]\n| align=\"center\" | 61st\n| [[Holden VY Commodore]]\n| [[Paul Morris Motorsport]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | 2005\n| [[2005 Australian Carrera Cup Championship|Australian Carrera Cup Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" | 10th\n| [[Porsche 911 GT3 Cup Type 996]]\n| Glenfords / Hitachi / Sirromet\n|-\n| [[2005 V8 Supercar Championship Series|V8 Supercar