\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n! width=\"10%\"| Photo\n! Model\n! Origin\n! Quantity\n! Notes\n|-\n! style=\"background:lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | Systems\n|-\n|[[File:Rcl106lat2.jpg|120px]]||[[M40 recoilless rifle]]\n|{{Flagu|United States}}\n|200<ref name=\"asiapacificdefencereporter.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com|title=Myanmar Defence Weapons|author=Mg Han|accessdate=29 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221112919/http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com/#|archive-date=21 December 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|Anti Tank Weapon\n|-\n|[[File:M3E1.jpg|120px]]||[[Carl Gustav recoilless rifle]]\n|{{Flagu|Sweden}}\n|1000<ref name=\"asiapacificdefencereporter.com\"/>\n|Anti Tank Weapon\n|-\n| [[File:RPG-7V_-_Interpolitex-2009.jpg|120px]]||[[RPG-7|RPG-7/RPG]]\n|{{Flagu|USSR}}\n|\n|Anti Tank Weapon\n|}\n \n==Weapons==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"text-align: left; background: #aabccc;\"|Name\n! style=\"text-align: left; background: #aabccc;\"|Type\n! style=\"text-align: left; background: #aabccc;\"|Versions\n! style=\"text-align: left; background: #aabccc;\"|Ammunition\n! style=\"text-align: left; background: #aabccc;\"|Origin\n! style=\"text-align: left; background: #aabccc;\"|Picture\n|-----\n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[Browning Hi-Power]]<ref name=\"jones2009\">Jones, Richard D. ''Jane's Infantry Weapons 2009/2010''. Jane's Information Group; 35th edition (27 January 2009). {{ISBN|978-0-7106-2869-5}}.</ref>\n| Side Arm\n|\n|[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]\n|{{Flagu|Belgium}}\n| [[File:Browning 9mm Pistol MOD 45151558.jpg|200px]]\n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[SIG Sauer P226|MA-5 MK III]]<ref name=\"jones2009\"/>\n| Side Arm\n|\n|9\u00d719mm Parabellum\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n| [[File:SIG Sauer P226 neu.jpg|left|200px]] \n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[Glock|MA-5 MKII]]\n| Side Arm\n|\n|9\u00d719mm Parabellum\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n| [[File:Glock 17 (6825676904).jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[TZ-45|BA-52]]\n| Submachine Gun\n|\n|9\u00d719mm Parabellum\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n| [[File:TZ-45.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[Uzi|BA-93]]\n| Submachine Gun\n|\n|9\u00d719mm Parabellum\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n|[[File:1952 General von Horn IMI Uzi 001 (cropped).jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[Uzi|BA-94/MA-13]]\n| Submachine Gun\n|\n|9\u00d719mm Parabellum\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n|[[File:Uzi of the israeli armed forces.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[M1 Carbine]]\n| Semi-automatic carbine\n|\n \n|[[.30 carbine]]\n|{{Flagu|United States}}\n| [[File:WWII M1 Carbine.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[EMERK|MA1]]\n| Assault Rifle\n|\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n|[[File:Galil.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[EMERK|MA2]]\n| Light Machine Gun\n|\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n| [[File:IMI-Galil.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[EMERK|MA3]]\n| Assault Carbine\n|\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n| \n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[EMERK|MA4]]\n| Grenadier Rifle\n|\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{Flagu|Myanmar}}\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[QBZ95]]\n| Assault Rifle\n|\n|[[5.8\u00d742mm]]\n|{{Flagu|China}}\n| [[File:QBZ 95 PLA.png|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[QBZ97]]\n| Assault Carbine\n|\n|[[5.8\u00d742mm]]\n|{{Flagu|China}}\n| [[File:QBZ95 automatic rifle.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[SVD Sniper|MA Sniper]]\n| Sniper Rifle\n|\n|[[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]]\n|{{Flagu|Russia}}\n| [[File:Interpolitex_2013_%28536-15%29.jpg|left|200px]]\n \n|- style=\"background:#efefef; color:black\"\n| [[HK33|MA11]]\n| Assault Rifle