no, Yad Vashem] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20090719032015/http://www1.yadvashem.org.il/about_holocaust/lost_worlds/grodno/grodno_during_ww1.html |date=19 July 2009 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ynet\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-3376540,00.html|title=\u05d3\u05e8\u05db\u05d5\u05df \u05e4\u05d5\u05dc\u05e0\u05d9 \u05d1\u05d6\u05db\u05d5\u05ea \u05d4\u05e1\u05d1\u05ea\u05d0 \u05de\u05d5\u05d5\u05e8\u05e9\u05d4|date=16 March 2007|website=ynet}}</ref>\n\n<!--unused ref<ref name=\"zydziwpolsce\">{{cite web |url=http://www.zydziwpolsce.edu.pl/panel23.html |title=\u017bydzi dzisiaj. Tablica 23 |publisher=Fundacja Stefana Batorego |year=2010 |accessdate=23 July 2011 |author=A & K Wo\u017aniak}}</ref>-->\n}}\n\n==References==\n* [[Marek Jan Chodakiewicz]], ''After the Holocaust'', East European Monographs, 2003, {{ISBN|0-88033-511-4}}.\n* [[Marek Jan Chodakiewicz]], ''Between Nazis and Soviets: Occupation Politics in Poland, 1939\u20131947'', [[Lexington Books]], 2004, {{nobreak|{{ISBN|0-7391-0484-5}}}}.\n* [[William W. Hagen]], \"Before the 'Final Solution': Toward a Comparative Analysis of Political Anti-Semitism in Interwar Germany and Poland\", ''[[The Journal of Modern History]]'', Vol. 68, No. 2 (Jun. 1996), 351\u2013381.\n* {{cite book |last = Hundert |first = Gershon David |title = Jews in Poland-Lithuania in the Eighteenth Century: A Genealogy of Modernity |year = 2004 |publisher = [[University of California Press]] |location = Berkeley |isbn = 0-520-23844-3 |ref = harv}}\n* [[Antony Polonsky]] and [[Joanna B. Michlic]]. ''The Neighbors Respond: The Controversy over the Jedwabne Massacre in Poland'', [[Princeton University Press]], 2003 {{ISBN|0-691-11306-8}}. ([https://web.archive.org/web/20041228113559/http://www.pupress.princeton.edu/chapters/i7632.html The introduction is online])\n* [[Iwo Cyprian Pogonowski]], ''Jews in Poland. A Documentary History'', [[Hippocrene Books]], Inc., 1998, {{ISBN|0-7818-0604-6}}.\n* David Vital, ''